%N A088896 Length of longest integral ladder that can be moved horizontally around the right angled corner where two hallway corridors of integral widths meet.
%C A088896 The set of values for the integral-widths corridors and longest ladder are merely the cubes of Pythagorean triples, viz. (A046083, A046084, A009000).
%C A088896 The corridors' widths may be parametrically expressed as d*(sin x)^3 and d*(cos x)^3, for a longest ladder length d making an angle x with one of the corridors.
%C A088896 A given ladder, however, is maximum-corner-bending for a family of infinite pairs of perpendicular corridor widths and that the envelope of the maximum bending positions is that of a sliding rod against the outer wall, which is a branch of an astroid or four-cusped hypocycloid.
